text: The High Speed Rail (West Midlands – Crewe) Bill Select Committee is a select committee of the House of Commons in the Parliament of the United Kingdom. The Committee was established in 2018 with a remit to provide persons and bodies the opportunity to suggest amendments to the bill. == Membership == As of 31 March 2019, the members of the committee are as follows: {| class="wikitable" ! colspan="2" valign="top" |Member ! valign="top" |Party !Constituency |- | bgcolor="" | |James Duddridge MP |Conservative |Rochford and Southend East |- | bgcolor="" | |Sandy Martin MP |Labour |Ipswich |- | bgcolor="" | |Sheryll Murray MP |Conservative |South East Cornwall |- | bgcolor="" | |Martin Whitfield MP |Labour |East Lothian |- | bgcolor="" | |Bill Wiggin MP |Conservative |North Herefordshrie |} == See also == * Parliamentary Committees of the United Kingdom == References == == External links == *High Speed Rail (West Midlands - Crewe) Bill Select Committee Category:Select Committees of the British House of Commons
